#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For every field in the collection, an <markup>&lt;entry&gt;</markup> may "
"contain an element whose name is identical to the field name. If multiple "
"values are allowed for the field, then the letter <emphasis>s</emphasis> is "
"added to the field name to create an element, and each value is added as a "
"child of the element, as in the case of the author, genre, and keyword "
"fields above."
msgstr ""
"Za svako polje u kolekciji, jedan <markup>&lt;entry&gt;</markup> može "
"sadržavati element čije je ime identično imenu polja. Ako je dozvoljeno više "
"vrijednosti za polje, a zatim se slovo <emphasis>s</emphasis> dodaje naziv "
"polja za stvaranje element, a svaka vrijednost se dodaje kao dijete "
"elementa, kao što je u slučaju autora , žanr, a ključna riječ polja iznad."

#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As a result, if additional fields are added to the collection, the data file "
"will no longer conform to the DTD. However, &appname; uses a non-validating "
"&XML; parser, so additional fields do not cause problems."
msgstr ""
"Kao rezultat toga, ako se dodatna polja dodaju u kolekciju, datoteka "
"podataka više neće odgovarati DTD."

#. Tag: title
#: hacking.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Images"
msgstr "Slike"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: hacking.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"  <images>\n"
"   <image width=\"111\" format=\"JPEG\" height=\"140\" id="
"\"cf65a2f023b6cb9e9233323dca10ac7c.jpeg\" />\n"
"  </images>\n"
"]]>"
msgstr ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"  <images>\n"
"   <image width=\"111\" format=\"JPEG\" height=\"140\" id="
"\"cf65a2f023b6cb9e9233323dca10ac7c.jpeg\" />\n"
"  </images>\n"
"]]>"

#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Inside the <markup>&lt;images&gt;</markup> element, each image referenced by "
"an entry is listed, along with attributes describing the image's size, "
"format, and id. If the image is contained inside the Zip file, the element "
"is empty. Otherwise, the image data may be contained in the &XML; stream as "
"base64-encoded text."
msgstr ""
"Unutar <markup>&lt;images&gt;</markup> elementa, svaka slika je navedena "
"unosom, uz atribute koji opisuju veličinu slike, format itd. Ako je slika "
"sadržana unutar Zip datoteke, element je prazan. Inače, podaci o slici mogu "
"biti sadržani u &XML; stream as base64-encoded text."

